sudo apt-get install clamav
sudo apt-get install clamav clamav-update clamd
sudo freshclam
clamscan -r /path/to/directory
clamscan -r --move=/path/to/move/to /path/to/scan
clamscan -r --remove=yes /path/to/scan


Schedule Regular Scans:
You can schedule regular scans using cron jobs. For instance, to run a scan every Sunday at 2 AM, edit your crontab (crontab -e) and add a line like:

bash
Copy code
0 2 * * 0 clamscan -r /path/to/directory
sudo systemctl start clamav-freshclam.service
sudo systemctl enable clamav-freshclam.service

Fix “freshclam.log is locked by another process” Error in ClamAV

sudo systemctl stop clamav-freshclam.service

sudo freshclam

sudo lsof /var/log/clamav/freshclam.log
sudo pkill -15 -x freshclam

sudo systemctl disable clamav-freshclam.service
sudo freshclam

